    "Numbers to Ruth_": "It also harmonizes with the crucial date given in I Kings 6:1, that the building of Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]`'s temple commenced in the four hundred and eightieth year after the Exodus from Egypt and was completed in seven years. ONE OTHER INTRODUCTORY REMARK The book of Joshua 14:6-15, not only recites the story of Caleb's allotment by Joshua himself, but also records its conquest by Caleb, together with the exploit of Othniel and the story of Achsah, Joshua 15:13-19, all of which is repeated in Judges 1:12-15,",
    "Unknown": "ver. 23-27), and the advantage of being impoverished for his sake,"
